cs.RO, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on the development of a reactive robotic system, specifically a forklift controller deployed on a Lego robot. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the challenges that software engineers may face when using GR(1) synthesis for the development of a reactive robotic system. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses linear temporal logic (LTL) and GR(1) synthesis, which are topics related to logic in computer science. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the use of LTL specification patterns as an extension of the GR(1) specification language, which is related to programming languages. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of automated procedures for reactive synthesis, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence.
